{
  "texts": [
    "Our correlational analysis showed several noteworthy findings.",
    "The number of authors positively correlated with Quality and Reliability, as could be expected.",
    "However, Quality and Reliability did not display a substantial association with altmetrics scores, while only a weak association was observed with the number of citations.",
    "These results are disconcerting, considering the worldwide attention on aspects such as methodological rigor and replicability, which are facets that highly loaded on the Quality and Reliability component.",
    "Others have similarly remarked that rigorous research, including pre-registered replications, does not necessarily correlate with popularity in terms of citations (Akcan et al., 2013; Hardwicke et al., 2021)."
  ]
}